---
import SiteLayout from '../layouts/SiteLayout.astro';
---

<SiteLayout
  title="About No Lock-In Printer"
  description="Learn how No Lock-In Printer researches printer lock-in, subscriptions, refillable ink systems, Linux compatibility, and OpenPrinter updates."
>
  <article class="article">
    <p class="eyebrow" style="color: var(--amber);">About</p>
    <h1>Independent printer buying notes for people who want control.</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      No Lock-In Printer helps readers avoid printer purchases that depend on mandatory ink subscriptions, opaque cartridge restrictions, app-only setup, or weak local printing support.
    </p>

    <section class="article-section">
      <h2>What we cover</h2>
      <p>
        We focus on subscription-free printers, refillable ink tanks, toner-based alternatives, Linux and CUPS compatibility, and emerging projects such as OpenPrinter. The site is intentionally cautious with early hardware claims: unlaunched projects are tracked as watchlist items, not treated as proven products.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="article-section">
      <h2>How to read our guides</h2>
      <p>
        Early pages are research starting points, not lab-tested final rankings. Before buying, confirm current pricing, exact model numbers, regional driver support, and recent owner reports about firmware or third-party supplies.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</SiteLayout>
